DEPARTMENT OF COMPUTING

Postdoctoral Fellow / Research Associate (Ref.22011202)

[Appointment period: twelve to thirty-six months]

Duties

The appointee will assist the project leader in the research project - “Second phase of the Jockey Club diversity at schools project”.  The project aims to transform local schools into self‐learning organizations that are capable to manage student diversity effectively and efficiently in their school-based contexts through the development and enhancement of school‐based diversity infrastructures in three domains: data‐driven / data‐informed school practice, learning and teaching activities, and close collaboration.  He/She will act as AI Analyst and be required to:

(a) carry out implementation and support tasks to ensure student data platform and associated systems being effectively implemented at schools, and quality support services being provided to enable adoption;

(b) conduct trainings and coaching to schools, teachers and systems administrators/IT support to ensure that they can effectively use the platform and the data to enable appropriate profiling, reporting, analytics, and intervention for diversity management;

(c) conduct trainings to schools, teachers, systems administrators on the use of data platform, associated systems, dash boards, AI tools, and the use and analysis of data;

(d) assist schools in the use, processing, and analysis of data and the development of analytics reports or dash boards;

(e) promote and facilitate deeper and wider adoption and use of the data platform and related solutions;

(f) provide effective support services to schools and teachers on operational and functional matters related to student data platform and use of data;

(g) investigate and follow‐up problems or incidents related to the use of the data platform;

(h) communicate with schools and teachers on implementation, usage and adoption;

(i) develop, maintain and support dashboards, analytics modules and reports;

(j) assist in the tunning of AI and machine learning tools at school level;

(k) assist in systems testing to ensure quality systems and services; and

(l) assist in the organization of workshops, seminars, conferences and other events as needed.

Qualifications

For the post of Postdoctoral Fellow, applicants should have a doctoral degree or an equivalent qualification and must have no more than five years of post‐qualification experience at the time of application.

For the posts of Research Associate, applicants should have a master’s degree or a good honours degree with three or more years of research/relevant work experience.

For both posts, applicants should also:

(a) have at least 2 years’ experience in software development, system support and training/teaching, preferably with some project management experience;

(b) have excellent communications skills and be fluent in both written and spoken English and Chinese;

(c) be proficient in using IT applications;

(d) have some knowledge of the use of BI and AI tools; and

(e) be familiar with school environment and use of data in education.

Applicants are invited to contact Prof. Jiannong Cao at tel no. 2766 7275, fax no. 2774 0842 or email via "Apply Now" for further information.

Remuneration

A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered.  Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.

Application

Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now".  Application forms can be downloaded from  https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms. If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process.  The closing date for application is Thursday, 10 February 2022.  Applicants who are not invited to an interview within two months from the closing date should consider their applications unsuccessful.  Applications should be addressed directly to Prof. Jiannong Cao (please state Department ofComputing on the envelope).  The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.

